                                                <h2 class="tm-text-title tm-text-title-small">Game Play</h2>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="tm-bg-dark-blue text-xs-left tm-textbox tm-textbox-padding tm-white-header-body tm-white-border tm-2-col-equal-height">
                                                <p class="tm-text">Campus Wars is a turn-based strategy game. Each player must wait for their turns, and have the opportunity to shoot at 5 desired tiles on the game map. The purpose of the game is to sink all opponent ships, so the player must carefully inspect the map and guess the positions that an enemy ship may reside. 
                                                 </p>     
                                                 <p>
                                                 When a player or AI shoots at a tile, it will set a flag. If there was any opponent ship in that tile, the flag is set as correct-hit (red-X) and if the shoot is missed, flag is set as a simple white circle. </p> 
                                                 <p> When all parts of the ship is hit, it will be revealed. </p>
                                                 <p> Before the game starts, a player has the option to change his initial formation with one of the the currently available formations designed for the game. There are currently 4 initial formations. </p>
                                                 <p> There is also a simple score manager which counts a combo bonus, when you repeatedly hit the correct tiles. Your high-score will be saved inside the game. </p>                                       
